            <div>
               <h1>Artonomy</h1>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/artonomy/Artonomy_Header@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/artonomy/Artonomy_Header@2x.png" alt="My Image" />
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <ul>
                  <li>Purpose - Artonomy is made with creatives in mind. Artists of all mediums can post pieces that aren’t constrained by finicky algorithms or ugly file compressions.  Feel confident in advertising shops and commissions without the fear of being shadowbanned.</li>
                  <li>Objective - To design iOS and Android versions of a native mobile application that provides a space for artists to post their works without algorithms and ugly file compressions.</li>
                  <li>Role - UX & UI Designer</li>
                  <li>Duration - Nov - Dec 2021</li>
               </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>My Process</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/artonomy/Process@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/artonomy/Artonomy_Process@2x.png" alt="My Image" />  
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Research</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <ul>
                  <li>Problem - Many popular apps are social media platforms that aren’t made with artists in mind. These apps make it difficult for artist to advertise their shops or businesses. Many of these apps also constrict artwork with file compressions or specific shapes.</li>
                  <li>Audience - Artonomy is an app for artists, illustrators, sculptors, writers, and creatives of all mediums who want to post their artworks.</li>
               </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Ideation</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>User Flow</h3>
               <p>This user flow details a user’s path through the app. This path begins at opening the app and then utilizing several key features such as editing a profile or leaving a comment.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/artonomy/Artonomy_User_Flow@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/artonomy/Artonomy_User_Flow@2x.png" alt="My Image" />    
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>Sketches</h3>
               <p>I created sketches for iOS and Android screens using the user flow as a guide.</p>
