            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/artonomy/Artonomy_iOS_Wireframes@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/artonomy/Artonomy_iOS_Wireframes@2x.png" alt="My Image" />
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>Prototyping and User Testing</h3>
               <p>After finalizing styles for the wireframes, I created prototypes for Android and iOS devices. I had four participants complete several tasks in the prototypes and gathered their feedback. This feedback was used to alleviate several notable pain points in the app.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/artonomy/Artonomy_User_Testing2@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/artonomy/Artonomy_User_Testing1@2x.png" alt="My Image" />
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <p>Pain Point #1 - Tester found it unclear what image was being selected when the quick 		buttons are activated. To make this more clear, I made the selected image brighter in comparison to the other images.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/artonomy/Artonomy_User_Testing1@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/artonomy/Artonomy_User_Testing2@2x.png" alt="My Image" />  
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <p>Pain Point #2 - User found the “Explore” option to be redundant along with the search feature on the toolbar. I got rid of the “Explore” option on the home page and replaced it with a “meatball” menu.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Design</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>Final Screens</h3>
               <p>After adjusting the design to remedy pain points identified through user testing, and applying any remaining styling, the final screens are completed.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/artonomy/Artonomy_Final_Screens@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/artonomy/Artonomy_Final_Screens@2x.png" alt="My Image" /> 
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Conclusion</h2>
               <p>If I had more time to work on this project, I would have done more user testing. I received a lot of a valuable feedback from the few participants I had, so I would like to have a larger sampling of users to test in the future. I also would like to create additional screens and demonstrate more features in the app.</p>
            </div>
